org.arkanos.pivotal_analytics.printers

Class SVGPrinter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.arkanos.pivotal_analytics.printers.SVGPrinter

  • public class SVGPrinter
extends java.lang.Object
    The SVGPrinter class handles creation of SVG images. Implementation accordingly to Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG) 1.1 (Second Edition). W3C Recommendation 16 August 2011. This class is entirely based on static behavior!
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Matheus Borges Teixeira
    See Also:
    http://www.w3.org/TR/2011/REC-SVG11-20110816/

    • Method Detail

      • labeledLineGraph

        public static java.lang.String labeledLineGraph(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,int[]> data,
                                int min_value,
                                int max_value,
                                java.lang.String[] points,
                                java.lang.String indent,
                                int skip)
        Returns a SVG image with a line graph. All data must have a title and a content. A legend will be printed on the right side. All data arrays share the same X axis labels and must have the same quantity. The Y axis is always broken in 10 blocks, proportional to the max value. The image will be built in fixed proportions using width and height.
        Parameters:
        data - defines the data to be plotted on the graph.
        min_value - informs the minimum value inside the data set.
        max_value - informs the maximum value inside (or desired for) the data set.
        points - defines the labels for X axis.
        indent - defines the string which will prefix all printed lines.
        skip - specifies an amount of X axis labels to skip, in case of long sets of data.
        Returns:
        a complete SVG image with the plotted data in form of a String.

      • pieSlice

        private static java.lang.String pieSlice(int center_x,
                        int center_y,
                        int radius,
                        float percentage_start,
                        float percentage,
                        java.lang.String title,
                        java.lang.String color)
        Draws only a slice of the pie chart. This is a helper method for the main printer method.
        Parameters:
        center_x - defines the x coordinate of the center of the pie in the image.
        center_y - defines the y coordinate of the center of the pie in the image.
        radius - defines the radius of the pie.
        percentage_start - specifies where, in proportion, the slice should start.
        percentage - defines the size, in proportion, of the slice.
        title - defines the name (CSS class) of the slice.
        color - defines a color for the slice.
        Returns:
        the complete <path> node for the slice in form of a String.

      • percentualPieChart

        public static java.lang.String percentualPieChart(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,float[]> data,
                                  int width,
                                  int height,
                                  java.lang.String indent)
        Returns a SVG image with a pie chart graph. The start point for the data is the right side of the pie. The data is printed clockwise and is not bounded to 100% Please note if the sum of the content data is >1 it will start overriding.
        Parameters:
        data - defines the data with all parts to be in the chart.
        width - defines the image width.
        height - defines the image height.
        indent - defines the string which will prefix all printed lines.
        Returns:
        a complete SVG image with the divided pie graph in form of a String.

      • horizontalProgressBar

        public static java.lang.String horizontalProgressBar(int data,
                                     int max_value,
                                     int height,
                                     int width,
                                     java.lang.String color_fill,
                                     java.lang.String color_text,
                                     java.lang.String indent)
        Returns a SVG image with a progress bar. The bar is the whole image with its percentage in the center.
        Parameters:
        data - specifies the current state of the progress bar.
        max_value - specifies what value is considered to be 100%
        width - defines the image width.
        height - defines the image height.
        color_fill - defines a color for the filling by name or hex code.
        color_text - defines a color for the text by name or hex code.
        indent - defines the string which will prefix all printed lines.
        Returns:
        a complete SVG image filled according to the state in form of a String.

      • horizontalLoadBar

        public static java.lang.String horizontalLoadBar(float data,
                                 float max_value,
                                 int height,
                                 int width,
                                 java.lang.String indent)
        Returns a SVG image with a load bar. The bar is the whole image with its percentage in the center. Unlike the progress bar, this does not ignore values above 100%. The color of the bar will get a brighter red, if over 100%. The visual effect stops if value is higher than 120%.
        Parameters:
        data - specifies the current state of the progress bar.
        max_value - specifies what value is considered to be 100%
        width - defines the image width.
        height - defines the image height.
        indent - defines the string which will prefix all printed lines.
        Returns:
        a complete SVG image filled according to the state in form of a String.
